# Frontend Component Rules

## Component Structure

```typescript
// Props interface at top
interface ButtonProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  children: ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}

// Component with explicit return type
export function Button({ variant = 'primary', children, className }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button className={cn(baseStyles, variantStyles[variant], className)}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Styling Rules

### Tailwind CSS (Default)
- Use for layout, spacing, typography, colors
- Keep class lists readable (break into multiple lines if long)
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes

### SCSS Modules (Exceptional)
- Only when Tailwind is genuinely awkward
- Complex animations
- Highly specific component styling
- Never duplicate Tailwind utilities

## Component Patterns

### UI Components
- Accept `className` prop
- Forward refs when needed
- No domain logic
- Fully typed props

### Feature Components
- Can be domain-aware
- Co-located with hooks
- Import UI components
- Handle loading/error states

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include ARIA attributes where needed
- Support keyboard navigation
- Test with screen reader
